---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import ArticleSchema from '../../components/ArticleSchema.astro';
import FaqSection from '../../components/FaqSection.astro';
import { siteFromHost } from '../../content';
const site = siteFromHost();
const path = '/alternatives/klaviyo-alternative';
const title = 'Best Klaviyo Alternatives for Shopify in 2026';
const desc = 'Compare Klaviyo alternatives for Shopify by data depth, lifecycle complexity, channel scope, cost, and migration risk.';
const tools = [
  { name: 'Omnisend', best: 'SMB stores wanting accessible email, SMS, and ecommerce automation', price: 'Verify current contact and channel pricing', pros: 'Fast multichannel setup and Shopify-oriented workflows', cons: 'Channel costs and profile growth need discipline', source: 'https://www.omnisend.com/pricing/' },
  { name: 'Drip', best: 'DTC brands centered on repeat purchase and retention', price: 'Verify current contact-based pricing', pros: 'Commerce-focused journeys and reporting', cons: 'Less suitable for broad CRM or complex multi-channel operations', source: 'https://www.drip.com/pricing' },
  { name: 'Brevo', best: 'Merchants needing email alongside transactional or additional channels', price: 'Verify current send, contact, and channel pricing', pros: 'Broad messaging coverage and accessible entry point', cons: 'Some Shopify lifecycle modeling may require extra configuration', source: 'https://www.brevo.com/pricing/' },
  { name: 'Shopify Email', best: 'Small stores that want native campaign simplicity', price: 'Verify current Shopify allowance and plan limits', pros: 'Low-friction native setup', cons: 'Less depth for behavioral and predictive programs', source: 'https://www.shopify.com/email-marketing' },
  { name: 'Sequenzy', best: 'Teams prioritizing focused lifecycle ownership and revenue-state workflows', price: 'Verify current plan and integration coverage', pros: 'Clear sequence ownership and SaaS lifecycle orientation', cons: 'Confirm ecommerce-specific event and catalog requirements', source: 'https://sequenzy.io/' },
];
const faqs = [
  { question: 'Why do stores leave Klaviyo?', answer: 'Typical reasons include cost at list scale, excess complexity, unused predictive features, channel overlap, or a desire for simpler ownership. Profile hygiene may solve the first issue without a migration.' },
  { question: 'Which Klaviyo alternative has the deepest Shopify data?', answer: 'Klaviyo is often shortlisted for detailed event and profile modeling. Alternatives should be tested with the exact product, order, consent, and customer-state fields your flows use.' },
  { question: 'What must be exported before switching?', answer: 'Export consent history, profile and segment definitions, flow logic, templates, suppression rules, coupon behavior, and Shopify event mappings.' },
];
---
<BaseLayout title={title} description={desc} site={site} path={path}>
  <ArticleSchema title={title} description={desc} siteName={site.name} domain={site.domain} path={path} />
  <main class="container py-14 md:py-20">
    <nav class="mb-8 text-sm"><a class="link" href="/alternatives">Alternatives hub</a><span class="mx-2 text-slate-400">/</span><span class="text-slate-400">Klaviyo</span></nav>
    <header class="max-w-4xl"><span class="badge">Shopify migration guide</span><h1 class="hero-title mt-5">{title}</h1><p class="mt-6 max-w-3xl text-xl text-cyan-100">Klaviyo is powerful when a store can use its event model and justify its operating cost. The best alternative is the one that solves the specific problem—complexity, economics, channel scope, or ownership—that triggered the search.</p><p class="mt-5 max-w-3xl text-slate-300">This is a fit guide, not a universal ranking. Verify current product and pricing details from official sources before publishing or migrating.</p></header>
    <section class="mt-12 max-w-5xl overflow-x-auto rounded-2xl border border-white/[0.08]"><table class="w-full text-left"><thead><tr><th>Platform</th><th>Best fit</th><th>Pros</th><th>Tradeoff</th></tr></thead><tbody>{tools.map((tool, i) => <tr class={i === 0 ? 'highlight-row' : ''}><td class="font-semibold text-white">{tool.name}</td><td>{tool.best}</td><td>{tool.pros}</td><td>{tool.cons}</td></tr>)}</tbody></table></section>
    <section class="prose-shopify mt-14 max-w-4xl">
      <h2>Start with the reason for leaving</h2><p>Do not migrate because another tool claims to be cheaper or easier. First identify whether the pain is contact pricing, unused features, slow campaign production, data complexity, SMS cost, or unclear lifecycle ownership. Then choose a replacement whose operating model matches that pain.</p><p>For a fair comparison, run one welcome flow, one cart or browse flow, and one post-purchase flow. Check event fidelity, consent and suppression, template QA, reporting against Shopify orders, and the time a non-engineer needs to make a safe change.</p>
      <h2>Platform notes</h2>{tools.map((tool, i) => <section><h3>{i + 1}. {tool.name}</h3><p><strong>Best for:</strong> {tool.best}. <strong>Pros:</strong> {tool.pros}. <strong>Cons:</strong> {tool.cons}. <strong>Pricing:</strong> {tool.price}. Read the <a href={tool.source} target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">official source</a> and include contacts, sends, channels, seats, integrations, and migration time.</p><table><tbody><tr><th>Test first</th><td>Can the platform reproduce one revenue-relevant journey with the same Shopify event, exclusion, and measurement logic?</td></tr><tr><th>Watch-out</th><td>A lower subscription price is not a saving if it creates duplicate messages, manual exports, or missing attribution.</td></tr></tbody></table></section>)}
      <h2>Migration checklist</h2><ol><li>Export consent, profiles, segments, suppressions, templates, coupons, and flow screenshots.</li><li>Map every Shopify event and field used in a trigger, branch, personalization, or exclusion.</li><li>Rebuild welcome, cart, and post-purchase journeys in a test environment.</li><li>Test duplicates, purchase exits, unsubscribe behavior, rendering, and reporting reconciliation.</li><li>Launch in stages and keep the old journeys paused—not silently live—until the new paths are verified.</li></ol>
      <h2>Verdict</h2><p>Choose Omnisend for fast Shopify multichannel operations, Drip for retention-focused DTC work, Brevo for broader messaging, Shopify Email for native simplicity, and Sequenzy for focused lifecycle ownership. Stay with Klaviyo when its data depth is actively used and the team can govern the cost. Switching is worthwhile only when the new platform improves the operating model, not merely the logo.</p>
    </section>
    <FaqSection faqs={faqs} />
    <p class="mt-12 text-slate-300">Continue with the <a class="link" href="/apps">app profiles</a>, <a class="link" href="/compare">comparisons</a>, and <a class="link" href="/guides">operator guides</a>.</p>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>
